# Sequences 2

### 935 points

[This challenge](enc.py) is very similar to [Sequences 1](../sequences1/sequences1.md), with the biggest difference being the much larger numbers in [output.txt](output.txt).

I'll start off the same way as with sequences1 by dividing the first given output values by the character values in "CTFkom{"

The division gives me large numbers, but since they are integers i am probably on the right track. The challenge mentions `it is almost the same as in the first challenge`, so it is probably still Fibonacci. 

The first decrypted number is `20015607811858599783824170011388655520902816825430165001395756114785839377954976563754545479774575337784993917305364417540147470269022027227492587906417805` and with a Ctrl+F search among [the first 1000 Fibonacci numbers](http://www.fullbooks.com/The-first-1001-Fibonacci-Numbers.html) it is found as number 740.

Having a script to generate fibb numbers 740 to 740+46 would take too long, so i manually added them to the script and from there solved it the same way as the first challenge.
